A Space Shooter game is a classic arcade-style game where the player controls a spaceship and has to dodge, shoot, and navigate through various obstacles and enemies. The game is typically set against a scrolling space backdrop, giving an illusion of moving through space.

Key Features:
Player Spaceship: Ability to move in different directions and shoot projectiles.
Enemies: Various types of enemy ships or obstacles that move and attack in patterns.
Scoring System: Points awarded for destroying enemies and possibly for collecting power-ups.
Lives/Health: Player has a certain number of lives or a health bar.
Power-ups: Items that give special abilities or restore health/lives.
Level Progression: Increasing difficulty, different enemy types, or bosses as the player progresses.
Background and Graphics: Scrolling starfield background.
